In England, in the seven days to 30 January, there were 590,157 new confirmed cases (1,043.6 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 23 January, there were 639,204 new cases, and so the new cases have decreased by 8% (49,047 fewer cases). The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in England so far as at 04 February is 15,177,316 (26,838.7 cases per 100,000 population).
